The paper focuses on exploring and exploiting web archives through the use of semantic technologies, which are commonly used in information retrieval (cs.IR), digital libraries (cs.DL), and databases (cs.DB). The paper also proposes a distributed framework for building semantic profiles, which involves artificial intelligence (cs.AI) techniques such as natural language processing and entity recognition. Finally, the paper discusses the use of Linked Data, which is a common topic in computational linguistics (cs.CL).
